      "section": "26.5",
      "text": "Figure 26.5-1D (Continued). Basic wind speeds for Risk Category IV buildings and other structures.\n\nThis figure shows a wind speed map of the United States displaying basic wind speeds for Risk Category IV buildings and other structures. The map contains contour lines with wind speed values in mph (and m/s in parentheses), ranging from 115 mph in interior regions to 200 mph along the Gulf Coast, with special wind regions marked by dotted patterns.\n\n[Structured: {\"type\":\"map\",\"geography\":\"Continental United States\",\"parameter\":\"Basic wind speeds for Risk Category IV buildings\",\"contour_values\":[\"115(51)\",\"120(54)\",\"125(56)\",\"127(57)\",\"130(58)\",\"140(63)\",\"150(67)\",\"160(72)\",\"170(76)\",\"180(80)\",\"190(85)\",\"200(89)\"],\"special_features\":[\"Special Wind Region marked with dotted pattern\",\"Higher wind speeds concentrated along Gulf Coast and Eastern seaboard\",\"Lower wind speeds in interior continental regions\"]}]",
