      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.5-prov2",
      "type": "provision",
      "section": "26.5",
      "text": "6. Mountainous terrain, gorges, ocean promontories, and special wind regions shall be examined for unusual wind conditions. Site-specific values for selected special wind regions shall be permitted to be determined using the ASCE Wind Design Geodatabase.",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.94,
        "y_start": 0.82,
        "y_end": 0.85
      },
      "column": "full",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.5-body1",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.5",
      "text": "7. Wind speeds correspond to approximately a 15% probability of exceedance in 50 years (Annual Exceedance Probability = 0.00033, MRI = 3,000 years).",
      "cross_references": [],
      "bbox": {
        "x_start": 0.06,
        "x_end": 0.94,
        "y_start": 0.86,
        "y_end": 0.88
      },
      "column": "full",
      "metadata": {
        "extracted_by": "vision-clone",
        "qc_status": "pending"
      },
      "_source": "left"
    },
    {
      "id": "ASCE7-22-26.5-body2",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.5",
      "text": "8. The ASCE Wind Design Geodatabase can be accessed at the ASCE 7 Hazard Tool (https://asce7hazardtool.online) or approved equivalent.",
